t/videos\r\n  video_names_file: /home/ddbb/comma_video_compression_challenge_houdini_submit/public_test_video_names.txt\r\n=== Evaluation results over 600 samples ===\r\n  Average PoseNet Distortion: 0.00018542\r\n  Average SegNet Distortion: 0.00057103\r\n  Submission file size: 100 bytes\r\n  Original uncompressed size: 37,545,489 bytes\r\n  Compression Rate: 0.00000266\r\n  Final score: 100*segnet_dist + √(10*posenet_dist) + 25*rate = 0.10\r\n\r\n\r\n# does your submission require gpu for evaluation (inflation)?\r\nyes\r\n\r\n# did you include the compression script? and want it to be merged?\r\nno\r\n\r\n# additional comments\r\nI don't think this loophole should be counted as an official entry, but I was remiss to see https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/69 fail official evaluation because the archive.zip appears to be missing some dummy contents needed to be treated as a valid zip archive. \r\n\r\nIn theory you could embed the entire original video into the inflate.py script this way and score perfect 0s on the Pose and Seg Distortion, but that's a bit much. Still, if there's going to be a joke submission with a dummy archive, I wanted to see  at least a .10 score. So I took the clever architecture https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/82, and added some source-side correction streams for some minor score improvement.\r\n\r\nThis approach could be pushed much further, but it's not at all in the spirit of the competition so I don't think it's worth spending time on.","created_at":"2026-05-04T00:23:54Z","updated_at":"2026-05-04T02:36:34Z","closed_at":"2026-05-04T02:36:33Z","merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"06c5a2fc94dfeea173601b7586b355f7d61ff397","assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[{"login":"YassineYousfi","id":29985433,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5OTg1NDMz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/29985433?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/YassineYousfi","html_url":"ht